这些话我都听腻了。

180
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,760
I'm not going to take any more of your empty promises.
我再也不会相信你的空头承诺了。

181
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:46,760
This is the fifth time you stood me up in two weeks.
这是你两周内第五次放我鸽子了。

182
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:48,760
You need to get your priorities straight.
你得搞清楚什么才是最重要的。

183
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:52,760
I'm tired of you putting your job first all the time.
我受够了你总是把工作放在第一位。

184
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,760
Come on, Veronica.
拜托，维罗妮卡。

185
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,760
That's not fair.
这不公平。

186
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,760
I do care about you a lot.
我真的很在乎你。

187
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:57,760
You know that.
你知道的。

188
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,760
I try to...
我试着……

189
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,760
You know what?
你知道吗？

190
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,760
Maybe we should just take a break.
也许我们该暂时分开一下。

191
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:04,760
I need some time to think about where this relationship is heading.
我需要一些时间来思考这段关系的发展方向。

192
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,760
But, Veronica, would you listen to me?
但是，维罗妮卡，你能听我说吗？

193
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:10,760
There was a fire alarm at my office building today, and I was...
今天我们办公楼的火警响了，我正……

194
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:22,760
So, Marco, this phrase, to take a break, really reminds me of a Friends episode.
所以，马可，这个短语“休息一下”让我想起了一集《老友记》。

195
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:27,760
Yeah, that really famous Friends episode when Ross and Rachel were on a break.
是啊，就是那集著名的《老友记》，罗斯和瑞秋在休息期间。

196
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:30,760
And Ross, like, went with another girl, right?
然后罗斯就和另一个女孩在一起了，对吧？

197
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,760
Yeah, and then they definitely broke up after that.
对，之后他们肯定分手了。

198
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,760
Yeah.
嗯。

199
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,760
So that's one of the key issues, right?
所以这是关键问题之一，对吧？

200
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:39,760
If you're taking a break, can you start to date someone else?
如果你在休息期间，你能开始和别人约会吗？

201
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,760
I've got to agree with Rachel.
我不得不同意瑞秋的看法。

202
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,760
Really?
真的吗？

203
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:43,760
Yeah. No, you can't.
是啊。不，你不能。

204
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,760
You can't?
你不能？

205
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,760
So what's the point of taking a break?
那休息一下有什么意义？

206
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,760
You need some time away.
你需要离开一段时间。

207
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:49,760
You need some time to think.
你需要一些时间思考。

208
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,760
But you're not really broken up.
但你们并没有真的分手。

209
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,760
Exactly.
没错。

210
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:53,760
That's convenient.
那可真方便。

211
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,760
I don't know.
我不知道。

212
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,760
They were on a break.
他们当时在分手期间。

213
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,760
I agree with Ross.
我同意罗斯的看法。

214
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,760
Well, you would, wouldn't you?
嗯，你当然会同意，不是吗？

215
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,760
All right, guys.
好了，各位。

